en_266229_0	Secretary Defence, General (Retd) Shantha Kottegoda warmly greeted the new Commander of the Army, Lieutenant General Shavendra Silva when he paid a courtesy call on the Secretary Defence at the Ministry of Defence premises this morning (3).
en_266229_1	During the cordial discussions that ensued, both of them discussed security matters of relevance and how the future would hold for the Army.
en_266229_2	Towards the end of the interaction, Lieutenant General Shavendra Silva presented a memento to the Secretary Defence as a symbol of goodwill and appreciation.
